tral horn = extensor muscles","Dorsal area of ventral horn = extensor muscles; ventral region of ventral horn = extensor muscles","Dorsal area of ventral horn = both flexor and extensor muscles"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe spinal cord contains motor neurons that are organised in specific regions of the ventral horn. These neurons innervate different muscle groups, allowing for coordinated movement. The correct organisation is that the \u003Cstrong\u003Edorsal area of the ventral horn\u003C/strong\u003E contains motor neurons that innervate \u003Cstrong\u003Eflexor muscles\u003C/strong\u003E, while the \u003Cstrong\u003Eventral region of the ventral horn\u003C/strong\u003E contains motor neurons that innervate \u003Cstrong\u003Eextensor muscles\u003C/strong\u003E. This arrangement allows for the coordination of muscle movements necessary for various motor functions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDorsal area of ventral horn = extensor muscles; ventral region of ventral horn = flexor muscles\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the opposite of the correct arrangement\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDorsal area of ventral horn = flexor muscles; ventral region of ventral horn = flexor muscles\u003C/strong\u003E - This does not account for the extensor muscles\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDorsal area of ventral horn = extensor muscles; ventral region of ventral horn = extensor muscles\u003C/strong\u003E - This does not account for the flexor muscles\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDorsal area of ventral horn = both flexor and extensor muscles\u003C/strong\u003E - The dorsal area is specifically associated with flexor muscles\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The dorsal area of the ventral horn in the spinal cord is associated with flexor muscles.","The ventral region of the ventral horn in the spinal cord is associated with extensor muscles.","The organisation of motor neurons in the spinal cord reflects the function of the muscles they innervate."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Longo, U. G., \u0026 Denaro, V. (Eds.). (2023). Textbook of musculoskeletal disorders. Springer Nature","Hughes, S. H. (2022). The Musculoskeletal System: The Musculoskeletal System-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Frontera WR, Ochala J. Skeletal muscle: a brief review of structure and function. Calcif Tissue Int. 2015 Mar;96(3):183-95. doi: 10.1007/s00223-014-9915-y. Epub 2014 Oct 8. PMID: 25294644","Morrison BM. Neuromuscular Diseases. Semin Neurol. 2016 Oct;36(5):409-418. doi: 10.1055/s-0036-1586263. Epub 2016 Sep 23. PMID: 27704495"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59978"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18404"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59978","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59978"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-25T05:53:25+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-14T23:53:23+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11122"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74487"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"